24:19.959 --> 24:22.120
Good morning, Your Majesty.

24:22.754 --> 24:24.290
7:30, sir.

24:28.760 --> 24:29.840
Sir?

25:03.586 --> 25:05.201
Stay there.

25:08.383 --> 25:09.964
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

25:21.104 --> 25:24.471
I regret to inform you
the King has just passed away.

25:27.777 --> 25:28.983
(GASPS)

25:32.407 --> 25:33.943
(SOBBING)

25:57.807 --> 25:59.047
(EXHALES)

26:01.436 --> 26:03.097
(QUEEN MOTHER WAILING)

26:42.727 --> 26:44.888
Call the Foreign Secretary.

26:45.730 --> 26:47.095
Tell him,

26:48.399 --> 26:50.515
"Hyde Park Corner."

26:51.068 --> 26:52.683
He'll understand.

26:58.743 --> 27:03.203
-Has the Princess been notified?
-If you mean the new Queen,

27:03.915 --> 27:05.621
my understanding is not.

27:05.708 --> 27:08.745
Then I suggest we do so
before it breaks on the wires.

27:08.836 --> 27:13.375
We're trying. We're not exactly sure
where she is at the moment.

27:13.466 --> 27:16.549
We're trying to contact
the Governor in Nairobi.

27:23.476 --> 27:24.636
(SQUAWKING)

27:33.402 --> 27:34.391
(WHIRRING)

27:45.248 --> 27:46.579
(CAMERA WHIRRING)

28:18.614 --> 28:19.990
(ENGINE STARTS)

28:23.160 --> 28:24.195
PHILIP: Let's go!

28:30.501 --> 28:34.744
-MAN: We need to go.
-We can't, we haven't had the all-clear.

28:34.839 --> 28:37.205
You think any other reporters
anywhere in the world

28:37.300 --> 28:39.586
will be waiting for an all-clear?

28:39.677 --> 28:41.759
I've had the BBC on the phone again.

28:41.846 --> 28:45.680
The news is breaking everywhere.
They can't keep holding.

28:45.766 --> 28:50.100
-And no news on the Princess?
-No, sir. Is it a yes to the BBC?

28:52.648 --> 28:53.808
It is.

28:57.486 --> 28:58.475
(DOOR CLOSES)

28:59.989 --> 29:01.650
And God help her.

29:01.741 --> 29:03.356
(ENGINE STALLING)

29:04.702 --> 29:06.317
They keep trying to start the engine.

29:07.496 --> 29:10.238
All they have to do is make sure
the fan is off and wait.

29:10.750 --> 29:12.160
No! Stop!

29:13.628 --> 29:15.539
She's just... She's overheated.

29:15.630 --> 29:17.541
No, can I have that? Thank you.

29:17.632 --> 29:19.293
All you have to do

29:21.510 --> 29:22.670
is wait.

29:22.887 --> 29:24.923
It's all right. I was a mechanic during the war.

29:30.686 --> 29:32.972
This is London.

29:33.731 --> 29:37.770
It is with the greatest sorrow
that we make the following announcement.

29:37.860 --> 29:40.977
It was announced from Sandringham
at 10:45 today...

29:41.072 --> 29:42.983
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

29:46.369 --> 29:48.360
(SPEAKING LOCAL LANGUAGE)

29:50.831 --> 29:52.492
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

29:55.127 --> 29:57.243
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

30:06.305 --> 30:07.920
(PHONE RINGING)

30:08.432 --> 30:11.424
-...and then drive to Nanyuki.
-Nanyuki.

30:11.519 --> 30:14.056
Nanyuki, sorry.
In a closed car arriving at 10:30.

30:14.146 --> 30:16.728
MAN: Morris. Morris! Reuters for you.

30:19.402 --> 30:20.733
MAN 2: 1045, sorry.

30:20.903 --> 30:23.519
There'll be a demonstration
of units of the African Rifles.

30:23.614 --> 30:24.820
Christ.

30:26.075 --> 30:27.656
Hold on, would you?

30:27.743 --> 30:32.453
1300, drive to Nanyuki airfield
and board East African AinIvays C47

30:32.540 --> 30:35.373
departing on a 1330 scheduled flight to...

30:36.711 --> 30:39.327
MAN ON RADIO: ...as flags across the nation
are lowered in tribute,

30:39.422 --> 30:42.960
and news spreads
throughout our cities and villages,

30:43.050 --> 30:46.292
crowds gather to mourn King George VI.

30:47.555 --> 30:50.422
We are comforted by the knowledge
that he spent his ﬁnal hours

30:50.516 --> 30:54.475
in the happy company of his wife
and youngest daughter.

30:54.895 --> 30:59.059
For it is as a devoted family man
that we, as a nation,

30:59.150 --> 31:01.436
shall best remember him.

31:01.527 --> 31:02.983
They don't know.

31:03.070 --> 31:04.606
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

31:06.949 --> 31:08.735
Sagana. Now, man!

31:26.177 --> 31:27.462
Thank you.

31:31.849 --> 31:35.933
-WOMAN: How was Treetops?
-It was wonderful. We saw elephants.

31:36.604 --> 31:39.266
-MAN: There is fresh lemonade.
-Oh, that looks delicious.

31:39.356 --> 31:41.062
Welcome back, ma'am.

31:41.650 --> 31:43.982
Let's go. Let's drive, shall we?

31:47.073 --> 31:50.156
Ready? Steady? Go.

31:50.326 --> 31:52.237
(IMITATES ENGINE REWING)

32:13.682 --> 32:15.388
Princess Elizabeth?

32:16.936 --> 32:18.392
The Princess?

32:18.479 --> 32:19.594
(SPEAKS LOCAL LANGUAGE)

32:19.688 --> 32:20.894
In here?

32:36.705 --> 32:37.865
(SIGHS)

32:38.082 --> 32:39.492
(SPEAKS LOCAL LANGUAGE)

32:39.583 --> 32:40.618
Duke.

32:51.512 --> 32:52.752
(PANTING)

32:56.600 --> 32:57.851
Excuse me, sir.

32:59.186 --> 33:00.926
What is it, Martin?

33:03.107 --> 33:04.142
Hmm?

33:26.505 --> 33:28.996
MAN ON RADIO:
The profound sense of personal grief

33:29.091 --> 33:30.547
felt amongst his people today

33:30.634 --> 33:32.499
stems from their respect.

33:32.595 --> 33:35.052
-I'm very happy to...
-No, no, no.

33:36.265 --> 33:39.678
-I should be the one to tell her.
-Yes, sir.

34:33.447 --> 34:37.440
MAN ON RADIO: The King, who retired
to rest last night in his usual health,

34:37.534 --> 34:40.196
passed peacefully away in his sleep.

34:40.329 --> 34:44.163
The BBC offers profound sympathy
to Her Majesty the Queen

34:44.250 --> 34:45.865
and the Royal Family.

35:26.375 --> 35:27.831
(BREATH TREMBLING)

35:34.133 --> 35:35.418
(GRUNTING)

35:39.471 --> 35:43.714
Your Royal Highness,
this stage of the embalming process,

35:45.060 --> 35:46.891
it may distress you.

36:14.590 --> 36:16.376
Your Royal Highness.

36:28.270 --> 36:29.430
(CRYING)

36:34.068 --> 36:35.478
(SOBBING)

36:37.404 --> 36:38.564
Father.

36:40.616 --> 36:41.605
For you, sir.

37:26.954 --> 37:29.115
They're going to send you away,
but I won't let them.

37:29.206 --> 37:31.242
I'm going to tell my mother not to send you.
I won't...

37:31.500 --> 37:33.036
(SOBS)
-(GENTLY SHUSHES)

37:48.016 --> 37:49.301
It's all right.

37:56.608 --> 37:59.771
You're not going. I won't let you go.

38:00.863 --> 38:01.852
It's all right.

38:09.121 --> 38:11.112
Ma'am, may I have a word?

38:21.884 --> 38:22.873
(SNIFFLING)

38:23.010 --> 38:27.003
It appears Miss MacDonald
neglected to pack a black dress.

38:27.097 --> 38:28.507
We've called ahead to London,

38:28.599 --> 38:32.467
and something will be brought
onto the plane before you disembark.

38:32.561 --> 38:33.721
ELIZABETH: Right.

38:35.105 --> 38:37.482
And a word of warning, ma'am.

38:38.233 --> 38:40.724
A good manyjournalists outside.

38:44.823 --> 38:48.691
Royal correspondents mostly,
assigned to cover the tour.

38:52.164 --> 38:54.075
-Should I say something?
-No.

38:54.166 --> 38:55.906
That won't be necessary.

38:56.710 --> 39:01.044
Though it would help if we could decide
here and now on your name.

39:02.549 --> 39:03.789
My name?

39:03.926 --> 39:06.258
Yes, ma'am. Your regnal name.

39:07.262 --> 39:09.344
That is the name you'll take as Queen.

39:12.518 --> 39:14.258
Obviously his name is...

39:14.686 --> 39:16.597
Was Albert.

39:18.774 --> 39:22.642
And before he abdicated,
your uncle took Edward.

39:22.778 --> 39:25.190
Of course, his name was David.

39:25.280 --> 39:27.817
-What's wrong with my name?
-Nothing.

39:34.915 --> 39:38.624
Well, then, let's not overcomplicate
matters unnecessarily.

39:41.004 --> 39:42.835
My name is Elizabeth.

39:44.258 --> 39:46.624
Then long live Queen Elizabeth.

40:04.403 --> 40:06.735
So sorry about the dress, ma'am.

40:07.614 --> 40:08.603
No.

40:11.702 --> 40:13.033
All right.

40:14.538 --> 40:16.403
Ready when you are, ma'am.

40:26.508 --> 40:28.009
(CAMERAS CLICKING)

40:28.427 --> 40:30.839
(PEOPLE CHANTING IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

40:44.192 --> 40:45.853
(SPEAKS LOCAL LANGUAGE)

40:55.120 --> 40:56.735
(CAMERAS CLICKING)

42:56.867 --> 42:59.279
(BOY CHANTING IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

43:06.960 --> 43:09.201
(CONTIN U ES CHANTING)

43:37.199 --> 43:40.487
-It's the middle of the night.
-I couldn't sleep.

43:40.577 --> 43:43.034
No one in the country can sleep.

43:44.706 --> 43:47.288
I know one shouldn't believe
everything one hears...

43:47.375 --> 43:48.410
But?

43:49.878 --> 43:52.244
I was speaking with Jock Colville's wife.

43:52.339 --> 43:54.204
-Mary. Margaret.
-Margaret.

43:54.299 --> 43:59.043
She said that Anthony
went to see the King 10 days ago.

43:59.221 --> 44:00.631
What for?

44:01.181 --> 44:03.547
To express his concern about your age.

44:04.684 --> 44:08.176
Your leadership. Your incapacity.

44:09.189 --> 44:12.647
-And to ask him to bid you to stand down.
-That's impossible.

44:12.734 --> 44:15.316
The King would never engage
in such treachery.

44:15.403 --> 44:19.612
And Anthony would never dare.
I've been like a father to him.

44:19.699 --> 44:22.236
I've groomed him every step of the way.

44:26.581 --> 44:29.698
Well, ignore me then.

44:31.294 --> 44:32.955
It's probably nothing.

44:34.381 --> 44:36.588
Come on, it's probably nothing.

44:37.926 --> 44:39.666
What are you up to?

44:39.761 --> 44:42.047
It's my eulogy for the King.

44:42.889 --> 44:47.223
It's broadcast tomorrow
and the right words keep eluding me.

44:47.310 --> 44:49.847
They'll want you to fail, you know.

44:49.938 --> 44:51.303
I know.

44:51.940 --> 44:55.307
Anything less than perfect will be a disaster.

44:58.572 --> 44:59.937
Anthony, eh?

45:10.709 --> 45:12.290
I can't sleep.

45:13.753 --> 45:14.788
No.

45:34.858 --> 45:36.189
I'm sorry.

45:38.570 --> 45:40.026
You're sorry?

45:42.657 --> 45:44.113
I'm sorry.

45:44.701 --> 45:46.566
I thought we'd have longer.

45:48.413 --> 45:49.994
-MARﬂN:Maam.
(KNOCKS)

45:51.333 --> 45:53.198
Three hours to go now.

46:00.342 --> 46:02.583
What do you think will happen?

46:03.678 --> 46:04.758
VVhen?

46:07.390 --> 46:08.846
When we land.

46:11.394 --> 46:13.180
What will happen then?

46:21.696 --> 46:22.947
-Morning.
-Morning.

46:23.031 --> 46:26.023
The PM will not be joining us this morning.

46:26.117 --> 46:30.781
He is very much tired
from all the emotion of yesterday.

46:30.872 --> 46:33.454
-So, where is he?
-He's still asleep.

46:33.541 --> 46:34.747
(LAUGHS)

46:35.210 --> 46:39.419
So, in his absence, as deputy, Iwill preside.

46:41.716 --> 46:43.047
(CLEARS THROAT)

46:44.135 --> 46:46.467
-The Queen's flight...
-Wait a minute, Anthony.

46:46.554 --> 46:50.797
If you're presiding over the meeting
on behalf of the PM,

46:52.477 --> 46:55.139
shouldn't you be sitting
in the appropriate chair?

46:55.230 --> 46:57.471
I don't think that's entirely necessary.

47:09.577 --> 47:10.908
Very well.

47:24.759 --> 47:29.128
So, the Queen's flight is now over Italy,

47:29.222 --> 47:34.433
having left the El Adem airfield
in Libya at 5:00 this morning.

47:38.606 --> 47:40.107
MARTIN: Sorry to disturb.

47:45.864 --> 47:50.699
May I just say how very sorry I am
that we'll not be working together anymore.

47:50.785 --> 47:52.525
VVhy?

47:52.620 --> 47:55.157
I have to give way to Sir Tommy Lascelles.

47:56.082 --> 48:00.416
As private secretary to the Sovereign,
he's my senior.

48:01.463 --> 48:04.500
This is where I have to stand aside
for the great man.

48:04.841 --> 48:06.126
Martin.

48:07.385 --> 48:08.465
I'm so sorry.

48:14.976 --> 48:16.011
(SIGHS)

48:16.102 --> 48:17.262
Ma'am.

48:20.065 --> 48:21.930
PHILIP: What a nightmare.

48:22.609 --> 48:26.352
Charteris at least had one foot
in the real world.

48:26.446 --> 48:30.155
And was your man, our man, on our side.

48:32.285 --> 48:33.650
Whereas Tommy Lascelles,

48:34.579 --> 48:37.161
he’s stuck in the land that time forgot.

48:37.665 --> 48:39.656
(KNOCKS AND OPENS DOOR)

48:41.461 --> 48:43.076
PETER: You asked to see me, sir.

48:43.171 --> 48:44.502
(DOOR CLOSES)

48:44.589 --> 48:45.920
Idid.

48:47.842 --> 48:50.504
-Will you sit?
-Thank you, sir.

48:52.847 --> 48:56.681
I'd assumed that, following the death
of His late Majesty,

48:56.768 --> 49:00.135
you would,
at the earliest appropriate moment,

49:01.106 --> 49:03.893
be resuming your duties
with the Royal Air Force.

49:03.983 --> 49:05.189
Yes, sir.

49:07.320 --> 49:09.527
I mentioned this to the Queen...

49:11.157 --> 49:14.570
The Queen Mother, this morning,
who then asked me,

49:14.661 --> 49:17.619
quite unusually,
to ask you whether you might like

49:17.705 --> 49:20.868
-to reconsider such a departure.
-Oh, sir?

49:20.959 --> 49:24.668
She felt that you had enjoyed
an uncommonly close association

49:24.754 --> 49:28.463
with her late husband
and earned notjust his trust,

49:28.550 --> 49:30.791
but the trust and affection
of the whole family.

49:30.885 --> 49:32.136
Thank you, sir.

49:32.220 --> 49:35.553
In the light of this, she wondered
whether you might consider

49:35.640 --> 49:37.221
staying on in a new role,

49:37.725 --> 49:41.058
as comptroller of
the Queen Mother's household.

49:41.146 --> 49:43.558
-| see.
-A kind and generous offer,

49:43.648 --> 49:46.390
as befits the widow of a kind

49:47.986 --> 49:49.692
and generous man.

49:51.739 --> 49:55.448
But while I'm sure you're greatly flattered,
I don't expect you to accept the post,

49:55.535 --> 49:57.696
hence my discouragement of the offer.

49:57.787 --> 50:00.995
I didn't want Her Majesty to suffer
the embarrassment of a refusal.

50:01.124 --> 50:03.035
Why would I not accept, sir?

50:03.918 --> 50:06.330
Well, you're asking
the wrong question, Townsend.

50:06.421 --> 50:08.161
Why would you?

50:08.256 --> 50:10.872
You're a decorated war hero,
still in your prime.

50:10.967 --> 50:13.208
Comptroller of
the Queen Mother's household

50:13.303 --> 50:15.009
has no military associations.

50:15.096 --> 50:17.303
It would take you away
from your wife and children.

50:18.391 --> 50:19.927
After all, the person

50:20.018 --> 50:24.261
with whom you enjoyed the uncommonly
close understanding is deceased.

50:30.486 --> 50:32.738
Unless I'm missing something.

50:33.781 --> 50:35.612
Unless there is someone else

50:35.700 --> 50:38.533
with whom you enjoy
an uncommonly close understanding,

50:38.620 --> 50:41.327
which would make accepting this post
more attractive.

50:43.333 --> 50:45.198
I don't know what you're referring to, sir.

50:45.293 --> 50:47.579
Don't you, Group Captain Townsend?

50:48.004 --> 50:49.790
Husband and father.

50:52.592 --> 50:53.752
No, sir.

51:03.311 --> 51:04.926
You're probably telling yourself

51:05.021 --> 51:09.765
that because no one has confronted you
about it that no one can know.

51:10.860 --> 51:13.567
Allow me to disabuse you of that delusion.

51:14.781 --> 51:18.524
Within the close community
of those that serve the family,

51:18.618 --> 51:22.907
I regret to tell you, that talk, ugly talk,

51:22.997 --> 51:26.239
unbecoming tittle-tattle is of little else.

51:26.334 --> 51:30.202
Now, I'm well aware of the toll
that round-the-clock service

51:30.296 --> 51:33.208
takes on the private lives of those that serve.

51:33.299 --> 51:36.791
I am also aware of the feelings

51:37.595 --> 51:41.634
generated by continued close proximity
to the people you are working for,

51:41.724 --> 51:46.844
but I would hate you
to mistake those feelings for anything else.

51:58.449 --> 52:01.361
Will you thank the Queen Mother
for her kind offer?

52:06.958 --> 52:09.040
I should be delighted to accept.

52:09.752 --> 52:13.085
There's no rush.
Take your time to think it over.

52:13.715 --> 52:16.297
Seventy-two hours, a week.

52:17.385 --> 52:19.421
I want you to make the right decision.

52:19.554 --> 52:21.465
I already have, sir.

52:21.556 --> 52:23.012
The answer is yes.

52:23.725 --> 52:24.714
(DOOR OPENS)

52:25.518 --> 52:26.507
(DOOR CLOSES)

52:55.965 --> 52:57.421
Gentlemen.

52:57.592 --> 52:59.082
Winston.

52:59.927 --> 53:01.758
Impeccable timing.

53:06.768 --> 53:08.133
That's the one.

53:18.237 --> 53:20.819
Your Majesty,
I've been asked to give you this.

53:22.200 --> 53:24.691
And this, ma'am,
from Her Majesty Queen Mary.

53:24.827 --> 53:25.987
Thank you.

53:29.665 --> 53:31.075
Thank you, Charteris.

53:31.918 --> 53:33.374
I'll take over from here.

53:39.384 --> 53:41.249
-Thank you, Martin.
-Thank you, sir.

53:46.474 --> 53:47.839
Your Majesty.

53:50.061 --> 53:51.301
Martin.

54:11.082 --> 54:12.822
